    <!-- ==================== HELP & SUPPORT ==================== -->

    <string name="help_and_support">Help &amp; Support</string>
    <string name="help_support_description">Find answers to common questions about using Soukify or contact our support team for assistance.</string>
    <string name="frequently_asked_questions">Frequently Asked Questions</string>
    <string name="view_faq">View FAQ</string>

    <!-- FAQ Questions & Answers -->
    <string name="faq_question1">How do I create a shop on Soukify?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer1">To create a shop, navigate to the Shop tab and tap the "Create Shop" button. Fill in your shop details including name, description, category, location, and contact information. Once submitted, your shop will be visible to other users.</string>

    <string name="faq_question2">What categories of products can I sell?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer2">Soukify supports various categories including: Pottery &amp; Ceramics, Textiles &amp; Tapestry, Gourmet &amp; Local Products, Natural Wellness Products, Jewelry &amp; Accessories, Metal &amp; Brass Crafts, Painting &amp; Calligraphy, and Woodwork.</string>

    <string name="faq_question3">How do I add products to my shop?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer3">After creating your shop, you can add products by going to your shop page and tapping the "Add Product" button. Enter product details like name, description, and price. You can add multiple products to showcase your inventory.</string>

    <string name="faq_question4">Can I edit my shop information after creating it?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer4">Yes, you can edit your shop information at any time. Go to your shop page and look for the edit options. You can update your shop name, description, contact information, and other details to keep your customers informed.</string>

    <string name="faq_question5">How do customers find and contact my shop?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer5">Customers can discover your shop by browsing categories, searching by location, or using the search feature. They can view your shop details, see your products, and contact you using the information you provide (phone, email, or address). Make sure your contact information is accurate and up-to-date.</string>

    <string name="faq_question6">Is Soukify free for sellers?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer6">Yes, Soukify is completely free for sellers. There are no setup fees, monthly charges, or commissions. You can create a shop, list products, and manage your business without any costs.</string>

    <string name="faq_question7">How do I manage orders and payments?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer7">Soukify focuses on connecting buyers with local artisans and shop owners. When customers are interested in your products, they can contact you directly via phone, email, or the address information you provide. You manage orders and payments directly with customers, giving you full control over your business relationships and transactions.</string>

    <string name="faq_question8">Can I sell products in multiple categories?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer8">Yes, you can list products in multiple categories as long as they fit the category requirements. Each product should be listed in the most appropriate category to help customers find what they\'re looking for easily.</string>

    <string name="faq_question9">How do I delete my shop or account?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer9">You can delete your shop or account through the settings menu. Go to Account Settings, scroll down, and select "Delete Account" or "Close Shop". Please note that this action is permanent and cannot be undone.</string>

    <string name="faq_question10">What are the best practices for successful selling?</string>
    <string name="faq_answer10">To succeed on Soukify: 1) Take clear, high-quality photos of your products, 2) Write detailed descriptions including dimensions and materials, 3) Set competitive prices, 4) Respond promptly to customer inquiries, 5) Maintain good ratings by providing excellent service, and 6) Update your inventory regularly.</string>

